<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-441-273  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 441 273.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 14 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>UGWUMP a big hit at MacWorld. (User GroupWelcoming/Unwinding/Meeting Place)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbare E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MacWorld ExpositionConferences and MeetingsComputer industryUser groupsTrade Shows.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UGWUMP A BIG HIT AT MACWORLD BOSTON, MASSACHUSETTS, U.S.A., 1990 AUG 14 (NB)-- This year's MacWorld Expo/Boston continued the practice started at lastyear's show of providing a  User Group Welcoming/Unwinding/Meeting Place(UGWUMP) at the World Trade Center.andP;  The show managers, Mitch HallAssociates, donated the space, a large room directly across the hall from theApple Computer seminar rooms, for user group members to congregate and relax.andM;The room, sponsored by Apple Computer, Inc., Ashton-Tate Corporation,Bit-by-Bit, Central Point Software, Inc., Claris Corporation, Ehman, Inc.,andO;Laser-Mate, Leasing Systems, Inc., and Tektronix, Inc. was open during showhours all four days and featured &quot;Meetings of the Minds,&quot; informal sessionsfor information sharing, networking, and problem-solving within the usergroup community centered around newsletter editors, bulletin board SYSOPS,AHUG (Apple HyperCard User Group), public domain software librarians andmeeting organizers.andP;  It was manned by 24 room volunteers from the MacintoshSpecial Interest Group of the Boston Computer Society.andP;  (BCS-Mac).andM;Carol Lesiecki of The Boston Computer Society told Newsbytes that &quot;this is aplace for user group members to gather in an informal and relaxed non-commerical space to talk about common problems.&quot; She also mentioned that theactivity in the room was running somewhat ahead of last year when 455 usergroup members visited the room.andM;In addition to the Boston Computer Society, the New York Macintosh User Group(NYMUG) and the Berkeley Macintosh User Group (BMUG) playied an active partin this year's exposition.andP;  All three groups exhibited at the BaysideExposition Center while BMUG had an additional booth at the World TradeCenter.andP;  Steve Costa, a BMUG volunteer working  at the World Trade Centerbooth, told Newsbytes that sales of  tie-dyed BMUG T-shirts and public domainprograms on diskette and  CD-Rom were &quot;selling well ahead of previous years.&quot;andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19900811)</TEXT></DOC>